3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bybit calculates ENA/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC based on the premium between perpetual and spot prices. The funding fee equals position size × funding rate × 1, paid between long and short holders. Bybit's unified trading account allows seamless hedging across spot and derivatives markets. The exchange uses a time-weighted average of the premium over the 8-hour period, reducing manipulation risk compared to shorter intervals."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","ENA","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ENA represents Ethena's synthetic dollar protocol, creating unique funding dynamics tied to delta-neutral strategies and staked ETH yields. The token's price movements often correlate with DeFi yield farming trends and Ethereum staking rewards, creating predictable funding rate patterns. Mid-tier volume provides sufficient liquidity for medium-sized positions while maintaining volatility for meaningful funding rate differentials."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ENA/USDT funding rates on Bybit have shown cyclical patterns correlated with Ethena protocol updates and DeFi yield cycles. During high ETH staking yields, ENA funding rates tend toward positive territory as traders anticipate increased protocol revenue. Weekly patterns emerge around major DeFi protocol announcements and Ethereum network upgrades. The pair exhibits lower correlation with Bitcoin funding rates compared to major altcoins, offering diversification benefits. Average funding rates range from -0.05% to +0.15% per 8-hour period, with spikes during significant protocol developments."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Cross-exchange arbitrage opportunities frequently arise between Bybit and other platforms due to ENA's concentrated trading volume on select exchanges. Funding rate spreads of 0.02-0.08% per 8-hour period commonly occur during high volatility periods. Calendar spread arbitrage becomes profitable when front-month funding exceeds 0.1% while back-month contracts trade flat. Delta-neutral strategies work effectively by longing spot ENA while shorting perpetuals when funding rates exceed 0.05%. Bybit's low maker fees and unified margin system reduce execution costs for frequent arbitrage trades."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Management Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ENA's relatively small market cap creates higher slippage risk during large position adjustments, requiring careful position sizing. Protocol-specific risks include potential changes to Ethena's delta-neutral strategy or regulatory concerns around synthetic dollars. Funding rate reversals can occur rapidly during market stress, particularly if Ethereum staking yields decline sharply. Liquidation risks increase during high volatility as ENA can experience 20%+ daily moves during DeFi sector rotations. Consider maximum position sizes of 2-3% of available margin to maintain safe leverage ratios during unexpected funding rate spikes."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often are ENA/USDT funding rates calculated on Bybit?","answer":"Bybit calculates ENA/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC. The rate is determined by the time-weighted average premium between perpetual and index prices over the preceding 8-hour period."},{"question":"What makes ENA funding rates different from other altcoins on Bybit?","answer":"ENA funding rates reflect Ethena protocol dynamics including staked ETH yields and delta-neutral strategy performance. This creates lower correlation with Bitcoin and major altcoins, offering unique arbitrage opportunities independent of broader crypto market sentiment."},{"question":"What position size limits should I consider for ENA arbitrage on Bybit?","answer":"Due to ENA's mid-tier liquidity, limit positions to $50,000-100,000 equivalent to avoid significant slippage. Bybit's order book typically supports up to $25,000 trades within 0.1% slippage during normal market conditions."},{"question":"How do Ethena protocol updates affect ENA funding rates on Bybit?","answer":"Major Ethena protocol updates often cause funding rate volatility as traders reposition based on expected yield changes. Monitor Ethena governance proposals and staking yield adjustments, which typically precede 48-72 hour periods of elevated funding rate opportunities."}]}]
